{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1a7e0fc9-f267-4f97-9963-16b5ee82b9d0","content":"Run **`dotnet workload update`**.\n\n- **`dotnet workload update`** — downloads and installs the latest versions of all installed workloads, aligning them with your current SDK. This is what you want after an SDK update.\n- **`dotnet workload repair`** — reinstalls the *same* versions already recorded. It fixes corrupted installations but won't pull newer workload packages that match your updated SDK.\n\nAfter updating:\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload update\ndotnet build\n```\n\nIf the build still fails, check that your `.csproj` targets a compatible `net8.0-*` or `net9.0-*` TFM for the SDK you upgraded to.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"51bbdce5-0b23-4392-bd53-47b3ecbe7c20","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the difference between `dotnet workload update` and `dotnet workload repair` to fix a .NET MAUI build issue after an SDK update. This is a general knowledge question that doesn't require tool usage — I can answer directly.","outputTokens":231,"requestId":"4847:21AFEA:56C8E96:5EDE9C4:69F3F9FF"},"id":"b9a8a300-5060-41da-a58c-e54b9c9c88f3","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:38.070Z","parentId":"56d8f39a-4fe1-4742-8d4f-9ebd948ce093"}
